               <history>
                  <origin>
                     <origDate notBefore="1900" notAfter="1999">twentieth century</origDate>
                  </origin>
                  <provenance>
                    <list>
                        <item xml:id="p1">
                           <desc>The catalogue entry at Mount Angel includes these statements about provenance and date: <q>“Dating is based on the script but also names in the various prayers,
                    one of which can be plausibly identified with office holding in 1932</q>; (cf. <locus target="#10r #18v #19r #37r #41v" facs="010 019 037 042">Fols. 10r, 18v, 19r, 37r, 41v</locus>).”
                    <q>“Ras Bǝrru, governor of Tamben (Ethiopia), 1932.”</q> <q>“Gabra Kidān Bǝrru, original owner, n.d. (ca. 1925).”</q></desc>
                        </item>
                        <item xml:id="p2">
                           <desc>The manuscript was donated to Mount Angel Library in 1980 by an “anonymous donor from Salem, Oregon.”</desc>
                        </item>
                    </list>
                  </provenance>
               </history>
